My jokes are what people
show up for. The BJs are shit.

12:35.776 --> 12:37.056
(electricity zaps)

12:37.254 --> 12:39.821
Oh, I went ahead
and ordered some appetizers.

12:39.972 --> 12:41.649
(branch snaps)
Enjoy.

12:41.831 --> 12:44.706
I, uh...
I am just now realizing

12:44.746 --> 12:47.022
I saw Mark McGwire flossing
in the restroom.

12:47.133 --> 12:48.770
I-I gotta thank him
for all the homers.

12:49.047 --> 12:50.229
Just one more time!

12:50.265 --> 12:51.654
And leave me under
a little longer.

12:51.709 --> 12:53.429
Let me really stretch my legs
in there.

12:53.493 --> 12:54.468
I can't do that.

12:54.504 --> 12:56.954
After five or six minutes,
you'll really die. Forever.

12:57.056 --> 12:59.043
Fine! Whatever!
Just give Daddy a taste!

12:59.101 --> 13:00.792
(Sighs) Okay, but this is it.

13:00.927 --> 13:02.658
You're so addicted
to the afterlife

13:02.713 --> 13:04.766
that you're missing out
on real life.

13:04.802 --> 13:06.112
I-I'm not some battery.

13:06.114 --> 13:08.018
I'm made of flesh and blood...

13:08.129 --> 13:09.520
and alkaline
and manganese oxide.

13:09.584 --> 13:10.847
But I have feelings!

13:10.937 --> 13:12.729
I'm just a normal guy
with feelings,

13:12.816 --> 13:15.755
who can power most
non-Samsung mobile devices.

13:15.883 --> 13:17.244
(electricity zaps, thud)

13:17.291 --> 13:18.457
(cellphone vibrates)

13:18.585 --> 13:21.494
Holy crap, I just got a retweet
from Toshi.

13:24.123 --> 13:27.466
Roger was right. It was crazy
to keep asking him to kill me...

13:27.561 --> 13:30.033
when I can just do it myself.

13:30.432 --> 13:32.599
(egg timer ticking)

13:34.208 --> 13:37.438
Hmm, a good scientist would
test this first.

13:37.660 --> 13:40.312
But if I was a good scientist,
then I'd also be a nerd.

13:40.488 --> 13:43.673
And I've made my stance on nerds
very clear.

13:43.851 --> 13:45.168
(click, electricity zaps)

13:45.286 --> 13:46.932
(groans)
(hissing)

13:47.054 --> 13:48.387
(continues ticking)

13:48.543 --> 13:49.974
(whoosh)

13:50.196 --> 13:52.196
♪♪

13:53.776 --> 13:57.767
I'm sure Stan wouldn't mind if
I took a peek at his progress.

14:01.278 --> 14:03.945
(Pages flipping)

14:07.074 --> 14:09.661
(gasps)
Stan hasn't changed at all!

14:09.853 --> 14:12.320
But he did nail my mannerisms.

14:13.546 --> 14:15.611
Stan! Oh, no!

14:15.746 --> 14:17.149
Stan, please!

14:17.206 --> 14:19.106
(click, electricity zaps)
(groans)

14:21.022 --> 14:24.008
Whoa! Oh, my god! Guys!

14:24.127 --> 14:27.400
Stan and Francine worked out
so hard, they fell asleep!

14:27.487 --> 14:28.906
ROGER: Shut up
and get those Fantas!

14:28.942 --> 14:30.196
I don't want
a history lesson!

14:30.261 --> 14:34.667
Okay, but I'm telling you,
it's super adorable!

14:36.608 --> 14:39.609
(laughing)

14:39.722 --> 14:41.534
MAN: Ugh, that was <i> terrible.</i>
(slurps)

14:41.589 --> 14:43.480
( laughs)

14:44.204 --> 14:46.673
If I could play multiple
characters like Eddie Murphy,

14:46.785 --> 14:49.027
they'd all be watching "Norbit"
together.

14:49.551 --> 14:51.649
(rumbling)

14:51.900 --> 14:53.885
(whoosh)

14:54.626 --> 14:57.006
Where am I?
Is that a Shamrock Shake?

14:57.141 --> 14:58.229
Why, yes, it is.

14:58.300 --> 15:00.232
But it's not even close
to St. Paddy's Day.

15:00.334 --> 15:02.280
Oh, my God.
I know where I am.

15:02.381 --> 15:03.535
I'm in Ireland!

15:03.571 --> 15:05.337
Um... you're in heaven.

15:05.381 --> 15:06.452
Yeah, right, buddy.

15:06.488 --> 15:08.789
If this were really heaven,
I'd have a Shamrock...

15:08.977 --> 15:10.465
shake! (slurps)

15:10.535 --> 15:12.681
But... that means I actually died.

15:12.781 --> 15:15.288
(slurps) Why didn't
the revival paddles fall on me?

15:15.405 --> 15:16.964
(slurps)
Because they fell on me!

15:17.040 --> 15:19.173
I can't believe
you killed us both!

15:19.229 --> 15:20.653
Well, technically,<i> you</i> killed us

15:20.689 --> 15:21.975
- when you got in the ay of my...
- Stan.

15:22.010 --> 15:23.053
Okay, all right.

15:23.089 --> 15:24.876
We could sit here all day,
arguing about

15:24.912 --> 15:27.045
whose homemade death machine
killed who.

15:27.192 --> 15:28.809
Or we could look
at the bright side.

15:28.853 --> 15:30.351
We can do anything we want here!

15:30.441 --> 15:31.974
Bam! My bum knee is fixed.
(ding)

15:32.167 --> 15:33.616
Bam! Ten-pack!
(ding)

15:33.671 --> 15:36.119
Bam! I have a tail.
Hell, yeah!

15:36.204 --> 15:39.138
(cries) Don't you get it?

15:39.289 --> 15:41.784
We're never gonna see
our kids grow up!

15:41.877 --> 15:44.247
We can make our own versions
of Hayley and Steve.

15:44.300 --> 15:46.868
But that Hayley doesn't even
have a mouth.

15:47.059 --> 15:51.050
And that's not even Steve.
It's Turtle from "Entourage."

15:51.198 --> 15:53.653
Yeah! Heaven!
I just don't get it.

15:53.789 --> 15:56.222
What was so horrible
about your life

15:56.322 --> 15:58.245
that you wanted
to kill yourself?

15:58.360 --> 16:02.091
I wasn't trying to kill myself.
I was escaping into my memories.

16:02.360 --> 16:04.110
When I heard about
my poor health,

16:04.291 --> 16:05.454
I-I know I played it cool,

16:05.490 --> 16:07.837
but... I wasn't as cool
as I was playing it,

16:07.873 --> 16:08.964
which was super cool.

16:09.000 --> 16:11.014
But beneath that Joe Camel cool

16:11.173 --> 16:13.079
was a Marlboro coward,

16:13.208 --> 16:16.107
terrified of the long,
slow decline of my body.

16:16.298 --> 16:18.631
Oh, Stan, I hear you.

16:18.713 --> 16:21.461
And I thank you for sharing
that with me.

16:21.739 --> 16:25.592
But the thing is...
you killed us, you idiot!

16:25.673 --> 16:29.168
We still had a lifetime
of memories to make on Earth,

16:29.265 --> 16:31.232
and you stole those from me!

16:31.393 --> 16:33.053
So as far as I'm concerned,

16:33.133 --> 16:36.318
you can spend the rest
of eternity by yourself!

16:36.412 --> 16:39.118
Francine, wait!
Give Turtle-Steve a chance.

16:39.154 --> 16:40.227
He's just like Steve,

16:40.324 --> 16:43.881
except he'll drive us anywhere
and he's always on ass patrol.

16:46.641 --> 16:48.408
(slurping)

16:48.625 --> 16:50.265
(voice breaks)
Just doesn't taste the same

16:50.301 --> 16:53.580
without Francine begging me
to stop for my own good.

16:53.829 --> 16:55.203
Excuse me, do you know

16:55.259 --> 16:57.261
if there's any way
to get back to Earth?

16:57.385 --> 17:00.678
Um, if you're looking to escape
the afterlife, I'd ask in hell.

17:00.765 --> 17:02.950
People are always trying
to get out of that craphole.

17:03.019 --> 17:05.419
Great. Thank you!
Sorry, one last question.

17:05.492 --> 17:08.137
If you're in heaven, why do you
have to work as a waitress?

17:08.230 --> 17:10.797
(chuckles) Oh, no.
I'm a slave.

17:12.032 --> 17:14.834
♪♪

17:18.301 --> 17:21.470
Hey, demon, is this obstacle
course the way back to Earth?

17:21.576 --> 17:23.675
Nah, that's the way
out of hell into heaven.

17:23.806 --> 17:25.743
ANNOUNCER:
Stepping to the starting line,

17:25.834 --> 17:28.401
Adolf Hitler!
(cheers and applause)

17:28.483 --> 17:31.985
MAN: Adolf is best remembered
for his work in World War II,

17:31.987 --> 17:35.255
and his legacy lives on
in Macklemore's haircut.

17:35.399 --> 17:38.825
He'll be making
his 453rd attempt

17:38.877 --> 17:40.959
at getting through the course
tonight.

17:41.029 --> 17:42.659
And he's off!

17:42.695 --> 17:45.530
Powering through
the quintuple steps with ease!

17:45.634 --> 17:48.334
No trouble
with the rolling log!

17:49.327 --> 17:52.774
Ooh! He tried to rush
the salmon ladder,

17:52.869 --> 17:54.363
and it looks like...

17:54.430 --> 17:56.197
(screaming)
(roars, crunch)

17:56.311 --> 17:57.906
No one ever makes it.

17:58.012 --> 18:00.680
But it's nice just to...
<i>get out of the house!</i>

18:00.849 --> 18:03.626
There's gotta be a way to get
me and Francine back to Earth.

18:03.721 --> 18:07.249
Yo, wings! Back to heaven
with you, you tourist.

18:07.355 --> 18:09.569
Think, Stan!
What do I know about the devil?

18:09.791 --> 18:12.591
♪ Devil with a moo mess,
moo mess, moo mess ♪

18:12.627 --> 18:14.296
♪ Devil-mmm-mmm, moo mess-ma ♪

18:14.354 --> 18:17.455
That's it!
He's always makin' deals.

18:18.800 --> 18:20.707
Hey, you're a bettin' man,
right?

18:20.802 --> 18:21.996
How 'bout this for a deal?

18:22.121 --> 18:23.878
You send my wife and me
back to Earth

18:23.958 --> 18:25.538
to live out the rest
of our lives.

18:26.110 --> 18:28.756
And...<i> yawn.</i>
What's in it for me?

18:28.826 --> 18:31.143
Next time I die,
I won't go to heaven.

18:31.281 --> 18:32.633
You get my soul.

18:32.669 --> 18:35.103
So you're willing to
give up heaven

18:35.183 --> 18:38.488
for a few more miserable years
on Earth?

18:38.666 --> 18:40.967
Yes, because all the heaven
I've ever needed

18:41.118 --> 18:43.255
was being with Francine
and my kids.

18:43.374 --> 18:46.408
Oh, wow, Stan.
I had no idea...

18:46.527 --> 18:48.824
that you were such a bitch!

18:48.973 --> 18:50.794
Fine, you got a deal.

18:52.016 --> 18:53.949
Oh, and when you get back
to Earth,

18:54.015 --> 18:56.082
tell Rachael Ray
to (bleep) off.

18:56.335 --> 18:57.770
She'll know what she did.

18:57.852 --> 19:00.324
That is not how you treat
another person!

19:00.427 --> 19:02.531
(smacks)
(flames whoosh)

19:03.608 --> 19:07.009
I can't believe they're dead!
(gasping)

19:07.115 --> 19:09.548
Now, I'm just as broken up
about this as you are,

19:09.640 --> 19:12.311
but we can't ignore the facts...
It's pretty chilly out,

19:12.347 --> 19:14.469
and neither of us knows
how to work the thermostat.

19:14.505 --> 19:16.670
Our only option
is to slice open the bodies

19:16.706 --> 19:18.479
so we can huddle inside them
for warmth.

19:18.613 --> 19:20.917
(inhales deeply)
Let's do it.

19:21.163 --> 19:23.284
I refuse to sleep in socks.

19:23.365 --> 19:25.008
(both gasp loudly)

19:25.266 --> 19:27.066
Stan, we're alive!

19:27.146 --> 19:28.315
Oh, thank God!

19:28.385 --> 19:30.054
What... happened?

19:30.110 --> 19:33.605
I guess someone realized
we needed more time here together.

19:33.641 --> 19:34.702
And this time around,

19:34.738 --> 19:37.291
I'm gonna make it last
as long as possible.

19:37.808 --> 19:39.643
(lowered voice) 'Cause then
I'm going to hell.

19:40.486 --> 19:41.914
What's with the knife?

19:42.043 --> 19:44.117
You shouldn't have to be
a goddamn electrician

19:44.179 --> 19:45.585
to live in this house!

19:45.808 --> 19:47.373
(door creaks open)

19:47.989 --> 19:50.560
Oh, is it cookie time already?

19:50.677 --> 19:53.428
Circle up, boys.
We have a game to play.

19:53.517 --> 19:55.852
No, Steve, you're late
for graduation!

19:56.034 --> 19:57.313
From pledging?

19:57.404 --> 19:59.346
No, from ASU!

19:59.481 --> 20:01.428
Come on, it's about to start!

20:01.603 --> 20:03.936
How?! I was only here
for a week.

20:03.985 --> 20:06.527
Remember when you asked
a question in the science lab?

20:06.608 --> 20:09.442
That was the minimum requirement
to graduate!

20:09.532 --> 20:10.661
Now hurry up!

20:10.705 --> 20:14.068
Oh, and get a speech ready.
You're also valedictorian!

20:14.230 --> 20:15.696
(applause)

20:15.984 --> 20:17.819
(feedback whines)

20:18.186 --> 20:21.287
♪♪ Heavy metal music playing...

20:21.322 --> 20:24.732
♪♪

